# metrics fold rules
# Scopes the `aglogs metrics` surface: the pure fold over unified transcript
# entries, the per-provider file-touch table, and the CLI that loads entries
# and emits the result as JSON.
#
# The fold is the Process axis of the eval run record, so a change here changes
# a measurement every downstream phase reads. The record package is the schema
# authority and is cross-repo, so a field change there invalidates the fold's
# output shape.
#
# The transcript types are the fold's input: UnifiedPart.Content is an
# interface{} that holds typed structs in-process and maps after a JSON round
# trip, so changes to the normalizers can silently break the fallback path.
# Paths are relative to the agentlogs repo root.

pkg/metrics/metrics.go
pkg/metrics/filetools.go
cmd/metrics.go
cmd/root.go
pkg/transcript/unified.go
pkg/transcript/normalizer_claude.go
pkg/transcript/normalizer_codex.go
pkg/transcript/normalizer_opencode.go
internal/provider/router.go
internal/provider/provider.go
../eval/pkg/record/record.go
tests/e2e/scenarios.go
